      "body" : "Creating incentives to connect to everything is less than ideal.  I'm generally positive about limited double spend messages, so long as care is taken to address the DOS potential. (though perhaps biased because I once posted proposing them too)\r\n\r\nOne positive point is if the involved txn have to pass the memory pool tests, then the existing anti-dos measures substantially limit dos potential.   This is especially true if each input can only have one dspend message in a nodes memory... in that case the worst case forwarding and memory burden from double spend notices is 2x. ",
